com.percussion.extensions.cms
Class PSCmsObjectNameLookup

java.lang.Object
  com.percussion.extension.PSSimpleJavaUdfExtension
      com.percussion.extensions.cms.PSCmsObjectNameLookup
All Implemented Interfaces:
IPSExtension, IPSUdfProcessor
public class PSCmsObjectNameLookup
extends PSSimpleJavaUdfExtension
implements IPSUdfProcessor

This class implements the UDF processor interface so it can be used as a Rhythmyx function. See processUdf for a description. This UDF is sepcifically designed to get name of the CMS object given the Locator for the object. The locator is assumed to have not more than three parts.

Note: This is very inefficient for the fact that it is a UDF which will be called per roww in the result set and we make an internal request per row. Ideally, we need to cache all CMS namelookups during server initialization and avoid internal requests. In that this is a temporary feature.

initLookupCache

public static Map initLookupCache(IPSRequestContext request)
Initializes the cache in the current request. If this extension is invoked more than once per overall request, but via more than one internal requests, since the cache is initialized in a clone of the request it's lifetime is then tied to each internal request and not the overall request. In this case this method should be called with the top level request object before the internal requests are made so that each cloned request used by the internal request has the same instance of the cache in it's private objects.

Parameters:
request - The current request, may not be null.
Returns:
The map used as the cache, never null.
